      • user

        public User user()
        [Note]: Before executing any calls, retrieve the authtoken by authenticating yourself via the Log in call of User Session. The authtoken is returned in the 'Response' body of the Log in call and is mandatory in all of the calls.

        Example: blt3cecf75b33bb2ebe

        All accounts registered with Contentstack are known as Users. A stack can have many users with varying permissions and roles

        To perform User operations first get User instance like below.

        Example: 

        Client clientInstance = new Contentstack.Client();

        OR: 
        Client clientInstance = new Contentstack.Client(authtoken);

        Returns:
        User
